# CODEOWNERS — RÉCOR
#
# Per Architecture V4 P10 § CODEOWNERS and Companion V1 P5.
#
# Rules:
#   - Every directory has at least one owner team.
#   - Stricter (≥2 teams required) on:
#       policies/                 (security + architect)
#       contracts/                (architect + integration)
#       services/frost-coordinator, libraries/rust/recor-crypto,
#         infrastructure/ansible (crypto + security)
#       docs/adversarial-corpus/  (architect + security + verification)
#   - .claude/ is architect-owned because its artefacts shape how every
#     future ticket is executed.
#
# Validation:
#   tools/ci/validate-codeowners.sh enforces coverage + stricter-rule
#   semantics + two-way team reference against docs/security/teams.md.
#
# Enforcement:
#   These rules engage GitHub's "Require review from Code Owners" branch
#   protection setting on `main`. Note: CODEOWNERS enforcement requires
#   the repository to be either public OR on a GitHub Pro/Team/Enterprise
#   plan. On a personal-account GitHub Free private repo, CODEOWNERS is
#   advisory (the rules are documented; review is not yet enforced).
#   See docs/security/branch-protection.md for the transitional posture.

